==English==

===Etymology===
From ecclesiastical Latin [[homousianus]], from Greek [[ὁμοούσιος]], from [[ὁμο]] ‘same’ + [[ουσία]] ‘essence’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/hɒməʊˈu:zɪən/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|homoousian}}

# Having the same [[essence]] or [[substance]], especially with reference to the first and second persons of the [[Trinity]]

